inn1.comm: starts with a length ball outside off, defended off the front foot towards mid-off
well outside off, swings away but mostly only after passing the stumps
ooh, that was just outside off, this time the ball came into the batsman, who was content to leave, doesn't miss off by much
ball jags away this time, starting outside off and going further away, Marsh shoulders arms
on middle and leg this time, punched back to the bowler
rounds off the maiden, this delivery was in the channel outside off, Marsh again offers no shot
Haddin gets the first run of the day by poking the ball towards point
angling across Marsh, the ball keeps a bit low this time, Marsh lets it through to the keeper
about a foot outside off, Marsh is content to shoulder arms
full ball outside off, jabbed towards backward point for a single
back of a length and just outside off, defended towards cover by Haddin
length ball slanting down legstump, Haddin looks to tap it away towards midwicket but misses and is struck on the pads
short ball outside off, dabbed with soft hands towards cover, Marsh thinks about the single but decides against it
lovely delivery, on a length just outside off and moving away a touch, 135kmh, left alone
same line but a little shorter, Marsh chops that towards backward point from pretty close to his body

dropped, driven forcefully towards Asif, who came at him at knee height, there was plenty of power behind that shot though and Asif can't hang on to it, the ball dribbles behind the non-striker's stumps and the batsmen hare through for a single
shot! gets nicely on the front foot and unleashes a classic cover drive for four

a series of appeals for lbw from Asif after Marsh is struck high on the pads, umpire de Silva wasn't interested, feeling the ball might have gone over the stumps, that pitched on middle and leg and was in line to hit but Hawk-Eye shows it would have sailed over the stumps
short of length outside off, played with soft hands towards cover point
gets a thick outside edge which sends the ball flying towards backward point for a single
a length ball heading for offstump, Haddin is early into his shot, gets a bit of an inside-edge and the ball swirls towards wide mid-on, lands safely
nothing much wrong with that stroke, Haddin continues to look to hit straight, caresses the ball to the right of the bowler, wonderfully timed
and another boundary to round off the over, an on-the-up cover drive played off the front foot, the outfield is pretty quick at the Waca and the fielders had little chance of catching up
Asif continues to peg away outside off, Marsh is happy to leave again
back of a length on middle and leg, defended back towards the bowler
Marsh gets onto the front foot to play that one but gets an inside-edge onto his pads, and dribbles to the off side
keeps it nice and tight around off, Marsh guides that one towards backward point for a single
shorter from Asif this time, line is immaculate again, just outside off, Haddin taps it off the backfoot towards point
slower ball, 119.2kmh, full and just outside off, worked towards point for a single

that was a pretty short ball, Haddin still plays it off the front foot, looks to club it down the ground but gets an outside edge that takes the ball towards deep backward point, Marsh sprints through for three
on the pads this time, clipped towards midwicket for an easy single
back of a length and outside off, steered down to third man by Haddin
on the pads again to Marsh, who gets easy runs again to midwicket
shifts his line to outside off, Marsh pushes hard at the ball and gets a healthy edge that hums wide of first slip to third man
slower delivery to end the over, 109kmh, full and on off, Haddin spots it early and checks his shot as he defends towards the bowler
short of length and just outside off, Marsh drops the ball towards the off side and wants the single but decides against it
Asif keeps it on a good length and just outside off, defended towards point
another spot-on delivery, on a length heading for off, Marsh blocks it towards the off side
Marsh shuffles across the stumps to look to push an outside-off delivery into the vacant gaps on the leg side, but he can only defend towards the bowler again

Kamran Akmal takes a superb catch to send back Marsh, who hasn't quite looked at his best today, Asif keeps nagging away just outside off, in McGrath-esque fashion, induces the outside edge which was flying to the right of Younis at first slip, Kamran flings himself full length and snaps that one up
length ball slanting into middle, Ponting shuffles across and turns the ball down towards fine leg
length ball heading into legstump, defended towards mid-on
back of a length outside off, Ponting defends
Ponting's penchant for the pull comes up again, short of length, and around middle and off, helped along towards fine leg
shortish ball on off, defended back towards the bowler
gets forward and clips the ball towards mid-on to get a single
length ball outside off, Ponting lifts his bat well above his helmet as he lets the ball through to the keeper
short and a bit of width, carved towards point
back to short of length and just outside off, defended back towards the bowler
blocked towards mid-off off the front foot
a bit of width on offer, Ponting slaps that hard towards backward point, where Fawad Alam latches onto the ball after moving quickly to his right
just short of a length, in the corridor outside off, Ponting gets forward and defends towards the bowler
slower ball, 121 kmh, whipped from outside off towards square leg
back of a length on off, shows the full face of the bat as he blocks towards the bowler
the Ponting pull makes another appearance, mistimed a bit and the ball trickles towards deep midwicket, hit off the bottom of the bat
deftly guides a ball that is just outside off towards third man
Rana belts out a confident lbw appeal, Ponting is hit just below the knee roll but was hit just outside off, the bounce on the pitch was also a factor, good call from the umpire
not too short but Ponting pulls again, with more authority this time, deep midwicket has more fielding to do
drops this one at his feet and rushes through for a single
charges down the track, Asif stays just back of a length, can't do much with it, hits it straight towards mid-off
slightly fuller and they pinch a single just to the left of Rao Iftikhar at mid-on
short delivery again, Ponting is still pull-headed about it, and even though the head falls away, he manages to keep it down
lovely, clean strike, jumps out of the crease again, trusts the bounce, takes it on its highest and lofts it over mid-off, don't matter that it is a shortish delivery
slower ball, on the pads, worked away with soft hands, gets a couple despite the presence of deep square leg
leaves this bouncer alone, too high - even for Akmal who gives away an extra

this - in tennis parlance - is running around a backhand and hitting an inside-out forehand smack for a winner. He steps out of the crease, Rana bowls the slower delivery, short too, gives him room and goes over cover
slower ball again, defended back
bowled him! what a comeback from Rana, full and straight and fast at 142ks, inches short of being a yorker, tailing in, and Haddin for a change looks to slog it to leg and plays all over it
back of a length, and Clarke gets off with another single to wide of mid-on, continuing from where he left at the Adelaide Oval
Ponting goes back and across and defends this one back to the bowler
stays back in the crease, slightly fuller delivery, but sees it off without trouble
Clarke shapes up for the pull, and pulls out seeing it bouncing too high for the shot, it also cramped him up a bit
fuller this time, still he is back of a length, angling in, defended to midwicket
angling in to the pads again, and helped away wide of mid-on
walks across the stumps and works a fullish delivery to wide of square leg for a coule
short and he pulls, all along the ground again, gets a single
well bowled, short of a legnth, just outside off, draws Clarke into the shot, and then the ball holds its line a touch and beats the batsman - 135ks
on the pads, worked away around the corner
full and wide, Clarke gets close to it, and drives with an open face, through the gap at point
flat, fast, down the leg side, and Ponting helps himself with a glance
slower this time, but way down the leg side, would be harsh to expect Akmal to collect this cleanly - it also kissed Ponting's thigh pad, a turn of events that the umpire missed
short outside off, beats Clarke on the late cut
steps out of the crease, gets to the pitch of it, and gets a single down to long-on
goes deep into the crease, and dead-bats an accurate delivery
looks to punch a back-of-a-length delivery outside off, gets a thick edge to third man
moves across and works this one wide of midwicket
oh my word, risky shot, Clarke almost walks across the stumps and flicks, the bat comes down just in time - for a moment I was anticipating a big lbw shout
stays back to a fullish delivery again, gets an inside edge while defending - they steal a single still

one cute single too many, Clarke is a goner! Clarke defends towards point, is called through by Ponting, but is slightly late in setting off, and Fawad Alam swoops, fields, throws in one fluid motion, hitting the middle of the middle stump at non-striker's end with Clarke way out of his ground
length delivery on the pads, pushed to midwicket
full delivery, around off, defended back
shorter, turning away, played towards point
looks to cut but it is too full for the shot, gets two off the bottom edge
shortish delivery, defended towards cover
flat, outside off, lets this one go through
flighted around off, White presses forward and defends
looks to work this for a single to leg, finds Younis Khan at midwicket

the pull-headed Ponting has hit a six, but he won't be watching too many replays of this, too early into that pull shot again, the head falls back, and the meaty top edge carries four rows into the stand behind the keeper
stays back again, pushed to mid-on
full ball, almost a half-volley, hit back to the bowler, on the bounce of course
helped away to fine leg for one
left alone outside off
punched off the back foot, gets a single to sweeper-cover
turn there, but shortish, and defended to cover easily
presses forward and defends to mid-on
plays back to one that he should be pressing forward to, the break gets an outside edge but all safe
shorter, hit back to the bowler
on the pads, turn this around the corner for a single
he has well left it for four! Pushes forward and across and shoulders arms, but it's too late by then and the ball catches the bottom edge and beats stumps and keeper both
pushing forward, gets slightly big on him from a length, defended towards point
runs this one down to third man for a single
nicely bowled, 134ks, but it's a nice legcutter, around off, straightening from back of a length, making him defend
short-arm pull this time, along the ground, gets a single
half-volley, driven straight to mid-off
goes back into the crease, punches it towards sweeper-cover
drives in front of his body, gets a single down to long-off
lunges forward, defends this one right enough of cover to get a single
almost does him in with a googly, White is looking to cut, but manages to get his bat in time before it squeezes through
into the pads this time, works it away for a single
lunges forward and shoulders arms, vintage Ponting, but he rarely does it against spin
and Rao gets something extra, bouncing slightly more off a length, White drops the bottom hand and defends
strays into the pads, White finds midwicket
back of a length, on the stumps, can't do much with it
and just like that, out of nowhere, White hits a scorcher, gets a length ball, gets under the slower one and hits a flat straight six - over mid-off
angling down the pads, fails to make contact but gets two leg-byes
slashes outside off, slashes hard, and the outside edge goes sailing over the slip
lunges forward and defends to cover
and again pushes forward and defends
flatter delivery, Ponting stays back, and plays with a dead bat

oh beautifully bowled, angling in, Ponting is drawn into working it to on, and it turns all the away across him, takes a big leading edge, and Akmal somehow manages to hold on to this one: off the chest, it gets stuck between the thighs, some four attempts in between - funny but true
angled across him, defended towards short third
again flighted around off, and he defends it towards point
starts with an accurate delivery, just outside off, turning in, defended
into the pads, can't get it past midwicket
angling in again, and turned around the corner
short, pushed to sweeper-cover, Hussey gets off the mark
flat delivery, pushed down the ground for a single
short again, and pushed down the ground for an easy single
tossed up outside off, cracked straight to extra cover
short of a length, turned the other away, back of the hand, punched off the back foot wide of midwicket for a single
short of a good length outside off, turned away, shouldered arms to that one
pushed it a little fuller, turned away and he let it go
gets forward, turns the face and works it away wide of midwicket for a single
gave it a little air this time, stepped forward and pushed it wide of extra cover for a single
waited for it to turn in, stepped  back and punched it hard through extra cover for a couple of runs in the deep
quicker through the air and kept it flat, gets outside the line and defends it in front of cover
keeps it flat again, steps forward and works it down towards midwicket
bowled it on a good length on middle, pushed it back down the pitch
pushed it short outside off, steps back and cuts it away towards deep point for a single
nicely done, fetches it from outside off, it lands full and he drags it between long-on and deep midwicket for a couple of runs
gets outside the line and defends it to point
pushes it slightly uppishly back to the bowler
tickled off the front foot behind square for a single
flighted outside off, gets outside the line and drives it just wide of midwicket for a single
short on the off, gets back and pulls it to midwicket for a single
short and wide, and cut away towards deep point
topspinner, White stays back and defends
pre-meditated paddle sweep, leaves stumps exposed, the ball turns past the stumps, misses the leg stump by inches, and has got his pad on the way and is still called a wide
flighted around off, not much room defended back to the bowler
shorter delivery, gives him time to push it down to long-on
doosra, nicely bowled, takes an edge outside off, and unluckily for the bowler it bisects Akmal and short third
toppie, defended down to mid-on
offcutter, front of the hand, Hussey cuts but doesn't make good connection
flicks it from outside off towards square leg for a single
flighted outside off, driven down to sweeper-cover
flighted around off, pushed to cover
fulltoss, misses out on it, hits it straight to cover
flat, angling across, punches it to off, can't go past cover-point
full, on the pads, worked to wide of mid-on for a single
slightly shorter, pushed to cover
tosses this one up, quicker through the air, and pushed to cover again
shorter, and this time he waits the extra second and beats cover for a single
flighted around leg, pushed to midwicket
a quick offbreak, goes back, makes room, and gets a single to short third man
starts back of a length, and they sneak a single after playing this with soft hands towards midwicket
nicely bowled, in-between length, no room, defended towards cover
gets a touch too full, the push-drive is well timed, but not far enough of mid-off
slower ball, on target, no room, can;t get under the length either, defends towards cover
shorter, doesn't rise up all that much, defended back to the bowler
looks to turn it to leg, but the ball is not straight enough, and again defends it back to the bowler
paddles this one from outside off, and since it's not hit too hard they come back for two
looks to force it through covers, gets a thick edge towards short third
the quicker ball, 105ks, on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
tossed up outside off, Hussey gets across and shoulders arms as it spins away
shorter this time, and pushed down the ground for a single
reads the straighter one this time, and cuts it past backward point, gets a couple
length ball, around off, flicked down the ground for one
short outside off, dabs it down to third man
good sharp bouncer, almost pulls it onto the stumps, does a bit too well at keeping it down - hits his own thigh
worked off the pads, gets a single
nice inswinging yorker, White manages a way out, digging it out with an open face and gets a single
dabs this one to wide of mid-off and comes through for one
short outside off, cut away, gets one to sweeper-cover
flat delivery into the pads, gets a single to square leg
topspinner, leaves it outside off, comes in with the arm, but not enough to concern Hussey
short and wide, and cut away for a single
another toppie, too full though, and played towards midwicket
quicker one, 110ks, and deadly accurate too, White does well to defend it back
length ball, stays back to it and defends
into the pads this time, and is turned away around the corner for one
slower ball, just outside off, defended
beaten outside off, holds its line slightly, and White is looking down at the wicket disapprovingly
tailing into the stumps, pushed towards midwicket
pushes forward, opens the face of the bat, can't get it past backward point
another doosra, another edge, gets a single to short third
nicely tossed up, coming in with the arm, defended towards short third
drives this fullish delivery to wide of long-off

White has perished - never really looked in actually, makes room, goes for the inside-out shot, but lofts it much too straight and Asif at three-quarters long-off moves well, judges well, holds it well behind his body, and is helped by the ball sticking to the tip of his fingers
topspinner, hurries Hussey into the cut, can't get it past point
and what timing right away, he has not much more than met it on his pads, just a slight flick and it goes past flying across the outfield, past mid-on
outside off, left alone
short ball, just outside off, stays back and defends
back of a length, around off again, and pushed to midwicket, staying at the crease so far
fuller, gets onto the front foot, and drives to mid-on
the first real misfield of the day, comes from Yousuf who is put under pressure at mid-on by Hopes who charges through for the single. The misfield eventually gives them two

nicely bowled, flat offbreak, Hussey gets a thick edge that goes past short third, and Rana gives a good chase, and sticks his foot over it and saves one run - could very easily have broken something down there in the ankle area
short outside off, hurrying him into it, gets a single
pulled away wide of midwicket, gets a couple
shoulders arms to this outside off
driven down the ground, wide of mid-off, gets a single
into the pads, helped away for a single around the corner
punched on the up, Rao gets a hand to it in his followthrough
pitched up, drives one bounce to Younis at cover
goes back into the crease, works it off his hip for a single
fulltoss, outside off, hit towards sweeper-cover
length ball outside off, driven for one to sweeper-cover
short and wide, and cut away to third man for one
short delivery, angling away, gets a single to deep point
nicely tossed up, gets some turn too, pushed down to long-on
topspinner, skids on, defends from deep in the crease
short and wide, cut to wide of sweeper-cover, and gets a couple
tossed up around off, turning away, played towards short third
short again, and pulled wide of long-on, and Hopes hustles back for the second. Afridi finishes with 10-1-44-1
that has slipped out of his hand, loop fulltoss, too high outside off, and pulled away wide of mid-on for four. Called no-ball for height
length ball outside off, gets a single to sweeper-cover
back to the length and line, just short of driving length, around off, Hussey can't do much with this one
short and wide, cut away fiercely, straight to Alam at point, and it goes through him for one
Asif you beauty! lovely offcutter, the same top-of-off attack, Hopes pushes half-forward, sees it is shorter than that and goes back, but by then the inwards movement has squeezed onto off and middle
shoulders arms to one outside off
back to close to off stump, defended with an open face
short and wide, cut away in the air, agonisingly wide of a diving Alam at point
ordinary delivery, well played, angling into the pads, he moves across a touch, and glances this fine of fine leg - only the 12th boundary of the innings
better delivery, around off, stays at the crease and defends
wide of off, no trouble in running it down to third man
driven on the up, but straight to sweeper-cover
length ball, just outside off, hit straight to Younis at cover
on a length, not much room, pushed down the ground, gets a single
looks for the sharp single towards point, but Fawad Alam is sharper
and again, Alam knows he can't let Hauritz off strike and he is charging in from point, good line and length from Asif too
little more width here, and he gets a single to third man this time
takes this from in front of off, and dabs it along the angle down to third man
bouncer, pretty accurate, and gets through another dot ball as Hauritz is not looking to pull it
short ball, sits up, and pulled away straight - it's a good shot because mid-on is up in the circle
pushes this one down to long-off for a single
that's right out of the screws, makes room, gets under this length delivery, and bang straight down the ground, a bit like the six hit by White earlier in the innings
flicked off the pads, can't get it past midwicket
fulltoss, hit well, clean timing, but can't beat extra cover
slower short delivery, Hauritz is early into the dab to third man, but again the aerial mis-hit evades Alam at point and lets them come back for two
drops and runs, gets an easy single towards cover
fuller, Hauritz presses forward and gets a single to long-on
full, almost a yorker outside off, driven with an open face, gets a single to sweeper-cover
offcutter, back of a length, outside off, nipping in, defended back to the bowler
yorker outside off, turns out to be a low fulltoss, but Hauritz can't do much with that
short ball, Hauritz premeditates the back-away-and-swing, misses by a foot
flicked from outside off, looking for two but has hit it better than he planned and gets just one to deep midwicket
and he gets a single to long-on, so he has bowled to his field: full, and turning into the pads
gets a fifty in front of his home crowd, sweeps this to deep square leg
comes down the track, is beaten in the flight, the inside half of the bat takes it wide of deep midwicket for two
short ball, heaved away to deep midwicket, will get just a single
inside edge onto the pad, and Ajmal fields the ricochet well to keep them down to a dot
sliced away wide of mid-off, uppishly but through the gap
yorker, squeezes it to point and gets a single
amazing shot, slower ball, and he short-arm-pulls, almost a sweep, superb placement wide of deep square leg
yorker outside off, gets just a single to cover-point
slower offcutter, Hauritz works it for a isngle towards short fine
yorker goes wrong, the low fulltoss is driven down the ground, again the placement is the key, wide of long-off - so quietly Hussey is doing his job again
Hauritz shows him all three stumps, this one comes out a fulltoss, Ajmal can't time it well, gets a couple to straight of long-on
slog sweep this time, is mis-hit, but lands just short of deep square leg
swept away fine, but straight towards fine leg
nicely bowled, the doosra. Hauritz has taken guard a foot outside leg, and it pitches a foot outside leg and spins away from him
another big swing, another big miss, well bowled Ajmal
chips this fulltoss down the ground, gets two
gets the yorker right this time, just a single to midwicket
superb timing from Hauritz, he is playing a nice little cameo here, Rana follows him as he makes room, it's not much more than a chip shot to this fulltoss, and it clears long-on
this is even bigger, Hauritz is playing a ripper, slower ball, and he gets under it and gives it the full whammy, rows behind long-on
gets the yorker right this time, dot back to the bowler
again a near yorker, and he digs it out for two, straighter of long-on
makes room, and swats this length delivery down the ground for a single and retains strike, big over for Australia
ho ho ho, this time he clears the longer boundary at the midwicket edge, comes down the track, maintains enough distance so that he can get under it and launches it across the line
what a 50 for Hauritz, steps out again, Hauritz bowls flat, gets a single to midwicket
misses the big sweep, and the topspinner misses the off stump not by much
top-edges the sweep, and because he hasn't got enough on it, it bounces in front of deep square and comes back for two. Cruel game for the bowlers
short and flat, and he has swept it for four, bisecting the two deep fielders on the on side, all his boundaries have been like this, not big shot but smart placement

leading edge and he is gone! looks to work it to leg for a single and the ball turns enough to take the front edge. Smartly, though, they don't cross even as the ball lobs to cover. As a result, Hauritz keeps strike
swipes this one across the line, gets one
full delivery outside off,d riven down to wide of long-off for two
pulls, mis-times, which means it hasn't gone fast enough to the fielder, and they come back for two
slower ball, wide of him as he backs away, creating enough distance, and it spoons off the top edge to extra cover where Afridi takes the dolly
good bouncer, follows the backing-away Hauritz, cleverly bowled
short ball again, this isn't that high, and Hauritz makes room and goes over backward point, doesn't get enough power in it but comes back for two

inn2.comm: full, hint of swing, tucked away, finds square leg, Shaun Marsh
swing again, beats him, but it's swinging down the leg side, hence just a stifled shout
swing again, beats him again, but too straight, and gives away leg-byes

oh what a ripper from White at second slip, smart bowling from Harris, this one doesn't swing in to Butt - three inswingers followed by the angling delivery, takes the healthy edge as Butt is tentative, and White at second slip dives full length to his left and takes it clean as a whistle
full, swinging away, and Younis lets it be
wicket-maiden for Harris, swing again, and Younis shoulders arms again
full delivery from Siddle too, driven with an open face, gets three runs wide of third man
Younis off the mark too, in-between length, gets an inside edge towards square leg for one
good clip shot off the pads, can't beat fine leg, though
beats Younis outside off, slightly holding its line outside off, but Younis is drawn into the poke
pushes in front of his body, gets a thick inside edge that finds the gap on the on side and gets him a couple
on target this time, just outside off, defended to cover by Younis
swing again for Harris, starts outside off, and Akmal shoulders arms
that's a jaffa, 145ks, outswinger that starts from close to off, and draws Akmal into the prod, misses the edge by inches
this time Akmal resists being drawn into the shot
sudden release of pressure with a short and wide, and Akmal's feet don't move as he throws his bat at it and is beaten
starts wide of off and swings away, and Akmal lets it go through to Haddin
another maiden from Harris, swinging away and still ending up around off, Akmal just pats it back to the bowler
seams in dangerously as Younis shoulders arms, not too far from off
good shot, overpitched and flicked away through the on side, gets three
cuts him in two, seams back in from back of a length, 144ks, and Akmal plays him way outside the line
too straight again, and clipped away for through the midwicket region
over-pitched, crisply hit back, Siddle does well in the followthrough
yorker, Akmal goes back in the crease and plays it to cover

edged and taken, Harris has taken two wickets without giving a run! And what a beauty to get his second wicket too, pitched just back of a length, just outside off, Younis has to play at it, and the away movement does the rest
lovely swing again, he is even starting middle and leg and shaping it away, defended watchfully
the inducker, the sucker punch, gets the inside edge on its way to the pads
first run given by Harris, and he can't control the swing this time and gives away a wide outside off
gets too straight with this full delivery, but driven straight to mid-on
slightly outside off, Yousuf shoulders arms
short and wide, cut away tentatively, straight to point, still no runs off the bat off Harris's bowling
fullish outside off, defended with an open face
over-pitched and driven away beautifully to the longest boundary at the WACA, opens the face slightly and drives it through extra cover in style
runs a length delivery down to third man for one
Siddle tries to bounce him but goes too high

gloves it down the leg side, Haddin dives but can't get there, it's a short delivery into the body and takes the glove fine, and Haddin dives perhaps a milisecond too early. An extra half a step was needed, says Ian Healy
fuller, outside off, Yousuf lets it go through
overpitched, this had to be put away, but Yousuf has hit it sweetly to mid-on
not that much swing this time, slightly shorter too, Akmal defends off the middle of the bat
full outside off, Akmal throws everything at it, and uppishly it goes wide of point, gets a single
angled into the pads, Yousuf misses, and it's just slid too far down the leg side
looks for the big, big outswinger, the pitch-leg-take-off type, not that much swing available here, and is lucky to kiss the shiny green pad on its way to Haddin
short and wide, and cut straight to point, not decisive with the shot
this one doesn't go to hand, full and wide, and only slight swing, he goes with the swing and drives it through cover
that's a smart shot, gets the width, gets under the length delivery, opens the face late and goes over cover
pulling the length back a touch, and Akmal can't play the front foot shot, and defends it towards point
slower ball, 124ks, Akmal stays on the crease and pushes it towards point
pinches a single, plays with soft hands towards point, and Yousuf calls early
extra bounce, 143ks, Yousuf thinks it's there for the cut, but the bounce beats him
presses forward and drives square of the wicket, can't beat cover-point
lucky here, with the fine leg up, eh bowls a gentle loosener on the pads, Akmal gets just one leg-bye
better this time, outside off, Yousuf shoulders arms
closer to off, Yousuf still shoulders arms, good leave
short, helped away to third man for a single
looks for the single to third man, but there isn't much room available
stands tall and punches a length ball, but not past point
presses forward and defends a length ball, middle of the bat
looks to late-cut, doesn't get it right but they still take single even though Haddin throws the stumps down
soft dismissal, goes for the forceful shot through the covers, but it's not short and wide enough, slightly closer than he thinks and the outside edge settles in Haddin's gloves
helped away off the pads to get off the mark

he's given him! looks to tuck him up with a short delivery into the ribs, goes down the leg side, and there is a noise as it passes Yousuf who is looking to get his hands out of the way. Big shout and given, it could have clipped the shirt too, let's wait for the replay. Tight, tight call, it did hit the shirt, but the Hot Spot shows a slight, the slightest, brush on the bottom glove too
right on target, just outside off, defended towards mid-off
bouncer outside off, he leaves it be
stays back and punches a shortish delivery to cover
short, sharp, outside off, left alone
back of a length, outside off, gets a thick edge to third man for a single
length ball, outside off, defended to mid-off
around the off stump, moving in with the angle, stays in the crease and defends
short outside off, again gets tall and back and across and defends
defended with an open face but the bowler oversteps
slower bouncer, Akmal backs away and throws the kitchen sink at it, but the ball is all dry through to the keeper
takes a sharp single, drops this with soft hands towards point and comes through
nice short delivery, lifting into the ribs of Alam, who is walking across the stumps, fends at it and keeps it down
this is the sharp bouncer that doesn't rise much, Alam has to bend really low in swaying out of the line
looks to force this through covers, but finds cover-point
short, gets width, cuts, but straight to backward point
nicely punched away, but straight to cover-point
back of a length, Akmal gets back and across, and defends it watchfully
looks to run this down to third man, but there is a gully in place to block that getaway shot
short outside off, and he lets it go through to finish the maiden over
starts off with a length delivery, angling across Alam, who opens the face and hits it to Ponting at point
slightly shorter, and he has nearly chopped it on, all is well for Alam, though
this time he lets Haddin earns his match fee by shouldering arms to this one
on the middle-stump line this time, Alam moves across and defends to off
fuller, driven down the ground, but straight to mid-off
short delivery, goes back and punches it through point for a single
starts the over with a bouncer, he ducks easily
back of a length, no room, defended back to the bowler
slower ball, turns out to be a low fulltoss on the pads, played towards midwicket
tries the same thing, aimed for the stumps, Alam defends well
looks to drive straight down the ground, gets the inside half of the bat, McKay gets a hand onto it
back-to-back maidens for McKay, again on target, no room available, and Alam defends off the back foot
length delivery, around off, Akmal stays on the crease and defends
short, into the body, pulled away to fine leg for one
tip and run, soft hands, towards White at short cover, but the early call got them through, and they get an overthrow too
looks to cut, doesn't get enough room to do so
thick outside edge as he looks to hit this through cover, will get a single down to third man
angled into the pads, Akmal misses on the glance, but Alam calls him through for a quick leg bye
what a good-looking shot, over-pitched, and hammered down the ground, high elbow, holds it for the photographers
shorter, and outside off, and he lets it alone
legcutter, bowled from wide of the stumps, gets it to hold its line upon pitching, defended off the back foot
bouncer, doesn't rise high, but it's safe for Umar as it is wide of off
short delivery, just back of a length, goes back and across and defends
length delivery wide of off, and defended off the back foot
length ball, moves across and pushes it down to mid-off
punches it from in front of stumps, but one bounce to White at cover
looks for open-face single, can't get it wide of Ponting at point
full and straight, looking for that lbw because of the shuffle, but Alam defends in time
slower offcutter, opens the face and gets a single down to third man
on target, on a length, headed for off stump, hit back to the bowler
gently tossed around off, pushed to cover
shorter, breaking away, cut away to sweeper-cover
hint of drift, pushed down to long-on, too full for the drift to trouble Umar
full delivery, pushed to sweeper-cover for a single
turn there, helped away towards short fine
overpitched, driven down to long-on for one
length ball angling down the leg side, stifled appeal for lbw, the ball strikes the pads and dribbles to short fine
shortish ball and a bit of width for Fawad, chopped towards point
Fawad continues to make his huge shuffle across, gets an inside edge to an offstump ball, sending it rolling behind square leg
on middle and leg, clipped behind square leg for a single
a short ball, Umar slaps it to square leg
on middle and leg, tapped in front of square leg by Fawad
short and wide, slashed towards point
carves it against the turn towards backward point, James Hopes scrambles across to his right to field
blocked towards midwicket
flighted on offstump, driven uppishly towards extra cover
a wristy whip sends the ball towards mid-on
outside off, Fawad gets forward and jabs the ball towards cover
length ball on legstump, defended towards mid-off
looks to chops it towards point, gets a bit of bottom edge towards cover
length ball on offstump, defended towards the bowler
well outside offstump, Umar looks to steer it towards third man, but misses
angling into the batsman, who turns it behind square leg
angling in from round the wicket, poked towards cover by Fawad
slows it down as Alam premeditates the sweep, but the batsman manages to keep it down towards fine leg
Haddin goes for a big appeal as it turns and bounces from leg stump, beating Umar's attempt at paddle; Asoka rightly calls it a wide
flatter delivery outside off, pushed to cover
back foot, gets low, drives against the spin of a fullish delivery, gets a single to sweeper-cover
pushes it wide of point, and takes a single
looks to defend off the front foot, beaten by the sharp turn
short, goes deep in the crease and pulls fine of deep square leg for two
beaten outside off, ends up playing inside the line of a straight delivery
gets in line this time, and defends to cover
hit powerfully, gets a single to cover, Hussey fumbles
short outside off, chopped away square of third man for two
this chop goes straight towards third man
almost squeezes through that bat-pad gap of the shuffling batsman, the inside edge hits him in the pad, could very easily have done a replay of his dismissal from Adelaide
slightly short, around off, defended off the back foot
lovely shot, moves down the track early, takes big strides towards the ball, gets right to its pitch and goes over cow corner
stays back expecting a flatter delivery, and late-cuts it for a single
genuinely short and wide, cut away to sweeper-cover for one
turning into the pads, turned around the corner for one
short, into the pads, hit to wide of mid-on for a single, another 50-run partnership between these two youngsters
short, doesn't quite come on, cut in front of square, Hussey fields at cover and flicks towards White at short cover, who some how flinches and ducks, and the two have a nice laugh
hits this wide of mid-off and gets a single
slower ball around off, presses forward and defends
back of a length, goes back and punches, towards cover
this time looks to run it down to third man, can't get it past point
shot! Clears the front leg, and smashes this length delivery inside-out over extra cover
flighted outside off, breaks away, takes a sharp single to short third man
reverse-paddle, gets it past short third, and takes a couple
angled across, straightens upon pitching, worked away for a single
short and wide and cut away, one bounce to cover-point
waits on this one and plays a little dab to short third for one
cuts a delivery that is not quite short, and straight to cover-point

Hauritz in action again, Alam calls for one cute single too many, hit straight and powerfully to mid-off this time, and Hauritz hits the stumps down and the desperate dive from Alam is not enough. On the full, the middle of middle
presses forward and defends a length ball to point
stays in the crease and defends
runs this one down to third man for a single
Afridi goes right away, pulls ff the front foot, gets a big top edge, straight over Haddin's head, almost a six
another top edge goes in the V behind the stumps, another four for Afridi
full, on the pads, single to long-on
slogs towards midwicket, gets a couple
what a beautiful shot, jumps out of the crease, gets under the ball and lofts him over long-on, into the second tier. No wonder crowds love him

and another six, what a statement to the top five, he hasn't quite got hold of this one, but this one still carries over wide long-on, the toppie seemed to have taken the outside half of the bat, but who cares?
backs away, Hauritz tosses it up even more, this time he plays with soft hands and gets a couple, all the fielders on the on side are on the boundary
Hauritz finall bowls the flatter, quicker one, Afridi looks to go inside-out, is beaten, but the ball misses the off stump
hint of swing right away, Umar looks to drop and run and hand over strike to Shahid, but Harris is quick, almost runs him out, would have been gone had he hit

No. 3 for Harris! Umar looks to drop it at his feet and get Afridi on strike, even softer than the previous time. Too soft it turns it out, as it bounces in the crease, and hits it bat again and rolls onto ever so gently hit the stumps enough to tickle the bail off its groove
he is on a hat-trick, what a beauty to get Rana, that's a mean delivery to get first up. Back of a length, around off, making him play, and then holding its line enough to take the edge
goes for the lbw, Rao is caught on the crease, and he just gets the bat down in time. For a second you would have anticipated an lbw shout
length ball outside off, pushed to cover
back of a length, just outside off, defended, double-wicket maiden
pulled away, another boundary for Afridi, square of deep square leg, he is playing a different game than the rest of the Pakistan team
low fulltoss, backs away, goes inside-out, takes a single to long-off
pushes thine one to cover, can't get a single
pushed down to mid-off, still can't Afridi on strike
thick outside edge, away from the body, Afridi back on strike
Boom Boom goes, another top edge on the pull shot, and this one lobs towards short third, Hauritz takes a few strides back and takes a safe catch
on target, stays back and defends
pokes at it outside off, is beaten, doesn't miss the edge by much
hits him high on the pads as he looks to turn this away to leg
slower ball, helped down to third man for a single
walks across the stumps and pokes  delivery outside off, misses
full ball around off, driven to cover
bouncer, Ajmal pulls, and this one passes inches away from his glove
goes for the big slog, doesn't get anywhere near the line
dropped, a rare fielding blip by Australia, the slower ball almost gets Ajmal but Hopes can't time his jump perfectly at mid-off
two overthrows there, Marsh being penalised for running the stumps down and keeping Rao in the crease
back and across, and defends outside off
defends off the back foot again
back of a length, defended
works this to on side for a single
nice bouncer, Ajmal does well to move out of the line
drops and runs, not too far off Harris but the early call does the trick
back of a length outside off, defended to cover
slower offcutter, can't get through the defences
plays a nothing shot, beaten by spin, but hit outside leg
sweeps, along the ground, gets a single
worked away off the pads, gets a single

bowled him! Ajmal should have known better, he plays the same tricks for a living! tossed up high, over the eye level, draws Ajmal into the big shot, and then it dips, suddenly falling a couple of feet shorter than it looked like, and then breaks in and goes through the gate
defends a flighted delivery watchfully
again defends this watchfully, towards cover
length delivery around off, pushed to mid-off
yorker, defended well
that's a better yorker, gets him foot out of the way, and gets the bat down in time
short outside off, and he shoulders arms this time
length delivery, and pushed away crunchily, gets a single
full delivery, Asif backs away and defends, straight from the Tailenders' Book of Batsmanship
guides this one down to short third man and takes a single
and Asif leaves this turning delivery alone
full, straighter, defended down the ground
tossed up, teasing Asif, who is having nothing of it and shoulders arms
Asif reverse-teases him with an attempt at a shot, a push down to mid-on
Hauritz bowls it flat outside off, played towards point
hits Rao in the thigh and they decide against a leg-bye
short, into the body, Rao gets too far across, and misses
fends at this short delivery, one bounce back to Harris
another short delivery, slightly outside off, doesn't have to fend at it

Ten wickets in two matches for Harris, and has he worked this one out beautifully or what? Four short deliveries, tucking him up, getting a short leg in, keeping him in the crease, and then sucker punch, full and wide, and the edge flies to right of Haddin who dives and takes it single-handed. No. 5 for Haddin too. I think Waqar Younis holds the record for most back-to-back five-fors in ODIs, he got three. Harris has got two
